Elasmopus alkhiranensis
sp. nov.
is primarily an Indian Ocean species (possible records include Red Sea, Persian Gulf, Madagascar , East Africa, South Africa , India , Sri Lanka , Mauritius ). Outside the Indian Ocean it occurs in the Mediterranean, where it could be a Lessepsian migrant (
Sezgin et al. 2007
), in the South China Sea (
Ren 2012
) and in Hawaii (
J.L. Barnard 1970
) Indian Ocean material described by the following authors is probably
